{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/acceleration","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events\">Device orientation events</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><em><code>acceleration</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/interval\"><code>interval</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/rotationRate\"><code>rotationRate</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Device Orientation Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceMotionEventAcceleration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventRotationRate\"><code>DeviceMotionEventRotationRate</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <strong><code>acceleration</code></strong> property returns the amount of acceleration recorded by\n  the device, in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meter_per_second_squared\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">meters per second squared (m/s²)</a>.\n  The acceleration value does not include the effect of\n  the gravity force, in contrast to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent.accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a>.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>Note:</strong> If the hardware doesn't know how to remove gravity from the\n    acceleration data, this value may not be present in the\n    <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a>. In this situation, you'll need to use\n    <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent.accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a> instead.\n  </p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The <code>acceleration</code> property is an object providing information about\n  acceleration on three axis. Each axis is represented with its own property:\n</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"x\"><code>x</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents the acceleration upon the x axis which is the west to east axis</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"y\"><code>y</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents the acceleration upon the y axis which is the south to north axis</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"z\"><code>z</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Represents the acceleration upon the z axis which is the down to up axis</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/deviceorientation/#ref-for-dom-devicemotionevent-acceleration③","title":"DeviceOrientation Event Specification"}],"query":"api.DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/acceleration/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/accelerationIncludingGravity\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent.accelerationIncludingGravity</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/devicemotion_event\" title=\"devicemotion\"><code>devicemotion</code></a> event</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/deviceorientation_event\" title=\"deviceorientation\"><code>deviceorientation</code></a> event</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events/Detecting_device_orientation\">Detecting device orientation</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events/Orientation_and_motion_data_explained\">Orientation and motion data explained</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The acceleration property returns the amount of acceleration recorded by\n  the device, in meters per second squared (m/s²).\n  The acceleration value does not include the effect of\n  the gravity force, in contrast to DeviceMotionEvent.accelerationIncludingGravity.","popularity":0.0002,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:10:34.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/devicemotionevent/acceleration","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/devicemotionevent/acceleration/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/1511e914c6b1ce6f88056bfefd48a6aa585cebce","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent","title":"DeviceMotionEvent"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent/acceleration","title":"DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration"}],"pageTitle":"DeviceMotionEvent.acceleration - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}